  "prompt": "What is expected from a partner interview at Ernst and Young?",
  "response": "During a partner interview at Ernst & Young (EY), you can expect the following:\n\n1. Professional Discussion\n- High-level strategic conversation\n- Focus on your professional experience\n- Assessment of your strategic thinking and leadership potential\n\n2. Key Areas of Evaluation\n- Technical skills and expertise\n- Problem-solving abilities\n- Cultural fit with the organization\n- Leadership potential\n- Communication skills\n- Business acumen\n\n3. Typical Interview Format\n- Generally 45-60 minutes long\n- More conversational than traditional structured interview\n- May include behavioral and situational questions\n- Potential case study or scenario analysis\n\n4. Potential Discussion Topics\n- Career goals and motivations\n- Professional achievements\n- Complex project experiences\n- Client interaction experiences\n- Understanding of industry trends\n- Your perspective on business challenges\n\n5. What Partners Look For\n- Confidence\n- Professional demeanor\n- Strategic thinking\n- Ability to articulate complex ideas clearly\n- Potential for future leadership\n- Alignment with EY's values and culture\n\n6. Recommended Preparation\n- Review your resume thoroughly\n- Prepare specific examples demonstrating skills\n- Research current business and industry trends\n- Understand EY's service lines and strategic priorities\n- Practice articulating your experiences concisely\n\nRemember, this interview is often a final assessment of your overall candidacy.",
